obamas-charlottesville-tweet/index.html|title=Obama's Charlottesville tweet is most liked in Twitter history|last=Schwarz|first=Hunter|date=August 16, 2017|website=[[CNN]]|accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== List : ==\nThe following table lists the top 20 most-liked tweets on Twitter, the account that tweeted it, the total number of likes rounded to the nearest hundred thousand, and the date it was originally tweeted. The notes include the details surrounding the tweet.\n\nTwo accounts have more than one of the most-liked tweets in the top 20: South Korean band [[BTS (band)|BTS]] have ten and former U.S. president [[Barack Obama]] has four.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center;\"\n! Rank\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Tweet\n! Posted by\n! Likes (millions)\n! Date\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Context\n|-\n! 1\n| style=\"text-align:left; font-size:9pt;\" | \"No one is born hating another person because of the color of his skin or his background or his religion...\" {{url|pic.twitter.com/InZ58zkoAm}}<ref>{{cite tweet|number=896523232098078720|user=BarackObama|title=No one is born hating another person because of the color of his skin or his background or his religion...|author=Barack Obama|date=August 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| align=\"left\" |{{sortname|Barack|Obama}}<br />@BarackObama\n| 4.4\n| align=\"right\" | {{dts|August 12, 2017}}\n|{{efn-ua|This tweet was the first of three tweets quoting a passage from [[Nelson Mandela]]'s autobiography, ''[[Long Walk to Freedom]]'', in response to the [[2017 Charlottesville attack]]. The accompanying picture, taken in 2011 by former White House photographer [[Pete Souza]], shows Obama visiting a day care center in [[Bethesda, Maryland]].}}\n|-\n! 2\n| style=\"text-align:left; font-size:9pt;\" | \"Kobe was a legend on the court and just getting started in what would have been just as meaningful a second act. To lose Gianna is even more heartbreaking to us as parents. Michelle and I send love and praye